{"pagetitle": ["Charterhouse Equity Partners LLC - Investments Since 2002"], "text": ["Investments Since 2002 Since our inception Charterhouse has completed investments in over 100 platform companies with a primary focus on management buyouts buildups and growth capital investments Our sustained and successful performance record is a result of our longstanding strategy of building strong partnerships with talented operating managers to build leading middle market companies Below is a list of companies that have been completed since 2002 when Tom Dircks took over leadership of the firm A listing of our AAT Communications Corp St Louis MO AAT Communications was one of the largest providers of wireless cell tower sites and site management services to the communications industry Through almost 20 acquisitions as well as organic growth the company became the owner operator and/or manager of approximately 7900 wireless communications sites in 47 states Amerifit Brands Inc Cromwell CT Amerifit was a leading consumer healthcare company that sells a variety of branded natural over-the-counter (\u201cOTC\u201d) and nutritional supplement products designed to meet specific consumer health needs Amerifit\u2019s key products included: ESTROVEN\u00ae the leading all-natural nutritional supplement brand addressing the symptoms of menopause; AZO the leading OT brand addressing pain relief and prevention of urinary tract infections and Culturelle\u00ae a leading probiotic supplement in the US Camelot Austin TX Camelot was a leading provider of services to youth and adolescents in both the alternative education and behavioral health markets The Company conducted its operations through therapeutic day schools residential treatment facilities and community-based programs where it managed programs for individuals experiencing a wide array of emotional and behavioral disorders In addition the Company contracted with public school districts to manage educational programs more conducive to the needs of \u201cat risk\" students Chamberlin Edmonds & Associates Atlanta GA Chamberlin Edmonds & Associates Inc was the market leader in providing specialized eligibility determination services to Americas hospitals The company guided uninsured patients through complex application processes to secure government and community reimbursement for uncompensated medical care expenses Specializing in federal and state disability programs the Company primarily served acute care hospital customers Boulder CO Rudis is a leading marketer manufacturer and distributor of certified organic and certified gluten-free breads buns muffins tortillas and related baked goods The Company primarily sells branded products through natural food chains independent health food stores conventional supermarkets and the club channel The Companys flagship brands include Rudis Organic Bakery\u0099 and Rudis Gluten Free Bakery\u0099CEO: Jane MillerChairman: Steve Mintz Bohemia NY FrontStreet is a leading national asset-light provider of integrated facility repair and maintenance services FrontStreet manages facility repairs and maintenance for customers with multiple locations in a process that involves vendor selection price negotiation dispatch coordination and billing The companys capabilities range from day-to-day repairs to refresh retail projects including planning design and construction as well as security services FrontStreet utilizes an extensive network of trade vendors CEO: Kristen BunnellChairman: Jay Gates Lason Inc Troy MI Lason was a provider of integrated information management and business process outsourcing solutions The Company served the financial services healthcare government manufacturing and industrial markets where accuracy privacy an security were top concerns With 54 locations and facilities management sites in 22 US states India China Mexico and Canada Lason utilized the latest technology surrounding data management scanning digital storage retrieval and delivery of sensitive data and documents to increase the efficiency and effectiveness of back-office and administrative functions LogistiCare Inc Atlanta GA LogistiCare was a leader in the non-emergency medical transportation service sector providing services to governmental agencies and other human services organizations that are typically under cost pressures but are required to provide recipients with access to and from medical encounters Organizations and state agencies contracted with LogistiCare to organize and to manage a credentialed network of local third-party providers to deliver the transportation on an outsourced basis MXenergy Inc Stamford CT MXenergy was a leading retail marketer of natural gas and electricity contracts to residential and small commercial customers in 14 states and within two provinces in Canada The Company offered variable-rate gas and electricity contracts and fixed-price gas contracts of up to three years in length NewPath Networks Inc Seattle WA NewPath designed developed and operated distributed antenna systems networks which enable wireless carriers to provide capacity and coverage in areas where building a conventional tower is impractical NewPath worked with telecommunications carriers including AT&T Verizon and T-Mobile to develop transmissions solutions in areas with high-traffic or difficult coverage situations NewPath\u2019s solutions involved the deployment of fiber and smaller non-visible antennas which overcame aesthetic considerations and provided flexible and scalable network infrastructure Oakleaf Waste Management Inc Hartford CT Oakleaf was a leading provider of outsourced waste logistics for customers with multiple locations in the United States Canada Mexico and Puerto Rico The companies services included: waste hauler contracting 24-hour customer service equipment rental recycling program management waste pickup scheduling vendor payment services and audit services Oakleafs equipment leasing division rented stationary compactors containers bales and other equipment to both commercial businesses and haulers Red Bank NJ RiverRoad is a provider of asset-light outsourced waste logistics solutions RiverRoad designs and implements waste and recycling programs that divert the waste stream reduce waste management expenses and help multi-location customers realize their sustainability initiatives RiverRoad leverages its purchasing power as a large customer of waste haulers to deliver significant savings to customers and to improve service accountability from vendors CEO: Kristen BunnellChairman: Jay Gates Suddenlink Communications St Louis MO Suddenlink is the seventh-largest cable television provider in the US providing video broadband Internet and telephony services to approximately 14 million residential customers and thousands of commercial customers in primarily medium-sized communities CEO and Chairman: Jerry Kent St Louis MO TierPoint is a leading provider of carrier-neutral colocation data center services With seven state-of-the art data centers located in Texas Oklahoma and Washington the Company is dedicated to protecting connecting and powering its customers mission-critical information assets TierPoint provides its customers with highly redundant power supplies first-class security and environmental controls premium bandwidth solutions 24 x 7 support and managed services that help maintain its customers?information systems CEO and Chairman: Paul Estes South Bend IN Towne is an asset-light provider of premium air cargo ground logistics transportation services expedited delivery and logistics management services The Company provides services on a nationwide basis from 61 terminal locations CEO: Tom DowneyChairman: Roger Gibson Birmingham AL Upstream is an owner and operator of outpatient physical and occupational therapy rehabilitation clinics The Company focuses on trauma sport work-related and post-surgical cases and has market-leading positions throughout the Southeastern United States in addition to business in Texas Arizona Utah Oregon and Colorado Through one of its subsidiaries the Company also enables access to managed care and indemnity insurance contracts for more than 1200 outpatient rehabilitation locations CEO: David Van NameChairman: Taylor Cole The Information on these pages is intended solely for the benefit of persons who might be aware of investment opportunities that would interest Charterhouse Charterhouses services are provided only to a limited number of private investment funds; Charterhouse does not make its services available to the public 2012 CHARTERHOUSE EQUITY PARTNERS LLC"], "pageurl": ["http://wwwcharterhouseequitycom/CurrentFundshtml"], "siteurl": ["charterhouseequitycom"]}
{"pagetitle": ["Charterhouse Equity Partners LLC - Private Equity Investing"], "text": ["Charterhouse Equity Partners LLC (\u201cCharterhouse\u201d) is one of the industry\u2019s most experienced middle-market private equity firms having invested in over 100 platform companies and hundreds of add-on acquisitions over the past four decades Working in partnership with entrepreneurial management teams to acquire controlling interests or to provide growth capital to growing middle-market companies Charterhouse is able to leverage its successful track record extensive knowledge base and broad network of resources to build middle-market businesses into larger more valuable enterprises This strategy has provided attractive returns to our management partners and investment partners As a direct investor in the US we seek to invest in growing businesses with enterprise values between $25 million and $150 million in which we can be a value-added partner Charterhouse strives to achieve the highest level of trust with its partners; TRUST being the key ingredient of any successful partnership As a testament to this multiple executives and management teams have chosen to partner with Charterhouse on more than one occasion The Information on these pages is intended solely for the benefit of persons who might be aware of investment opportunities that would interest Charterhouse Charterhouses services are provided only to a limited number of private investment funds; Charterhouse does not make its services available to the public 2012 CHARTERHOUSE EQUITY PARTNERS LLC"], "pageurl": ["http://wwwcharterhouseequitycom/"], "siteurl": ["charterhouseequitycom"]}
{"pagetitle": ["Charterhouse Equity Partners LLC - Team"], "text": ["Team Thomas C Dircks Managing Director (212) 584-3229 Tom Dircks began his career in private equity when he joined Charterhouse Group in 1983 after being a Certified Public Accountant at Price Waterhouse During the early years Tom was instrumental in analyzing diligencing structuring monitoring and realizing many of the Firms portfolio companies These included industrial companies in the steel textiles batteries furniture auto parts and electronic components markets and consumer and business services companies in the food apparel cable television retail and transportation sectors In 1991 he was appointed a member of the Firms investment committee and became directly responsible for sourcing and cultivating entrepreneur relationships and investment opportunities and led some of the Firms largest and most successful platform investments and buildups including Charter Communications Cross Country Healthcare and AAT Communications In the case of AAT Tom developed the plan to acquire control of this existing platform company and invest an additional $140 million of Charterhouse equity to build a significant company in the wireless tower sector At the time the industry was out of favor and he recruited Charterhouse Entrepreneur Jerry Kent who had previously built Charter Communications into one of the largest cable television companies in the US as CEO to execute the strategy Tom holds an MBA and a BS in Accounting from Fordham University and serves as a director of Charter Facility Services Upstream Rehabilitation and Cross Country Healthcare He previously served as a director of ATT Communications Oakleaf Waste Management Amerifit Brands The Camelot Schools Tierpoint and Charter Communications Tom also serves as a trustee of The Robert and Joan Dircks Foundation and as an Advisory Board member of The Medical Needs Foundation William Landuyt Managing Director (212) 584-3216 Bill Landuyt joined Charterhouse in 2003 after spending over 20 years with UK-based Hanson PLC and its affiliates most recently serving as the Chairman and CEO of Millennium Chemicals Inc a NYSE-listed diversified chemical company that had been a spin-off from Hanson PLC He had previously served as the President of Hansons $85 billion US operations as well as the Finance Director (CFO equivalent) of Hanson PLC the $185 billion parent entity Bill managed and was actively involved in Hansons substantial volume of mergers and acquisition activity across a variety of industries and transaction types He leads and manages a number of the Firms investments Bill began his career (with Tom Dircks) as a Certified Public Accountant at Pricewaterhouse Coopers He graduated from the University of Notre Dame with a BBA in Accounting He previously served as a Director of Towne Air Freight TierPoint MXenergy NewPath Networks AAT Communications and MP TotalCare Bill is also the Co-Founder of Celtic Charms Inc a non-profit therapeutic riding center for people with disabilities Steven Dircks Associate (212) 584-3246 Steven Dircks joined Charterhouse in 2013 He is primarily focused on assisting in the execution of new platform and add-on transactions along with monitoring existing portfolio companies Steven received his BBA in Economics from Loyola University Strategic Advisors Taylor Cole Strategic Advisor and Chairman of Upstream Rehabilitation (212) 584-3212 Taylor Cole joined Charterhouse in 1998 and served as a Managing Director until 2012 when he became a Strategic Advisor to Charterhouse He continues to serve as the Chairman of Upstream Rehabilitation Inc a current Charterhouse portfolio company Taylor was responsible for sourcing evaluating and executing new platform and add-on investments along with monitoring portfolio company activities within the Healthcare Services sector Prior to joining Charterhouse he was a member of the Investment Banking Division of Morgan Stanley & Co Taylor has been actively involved in a variety of speaking engagements related to private equity investing in the healthcare services industry and recently served as the Chairman and Keynote Speaker of the Capital Roundtable MasterClass on Private Equity Investing in Middle-Market Healthcare Companies Mr Cole also serves as Treasurer of the Health Care private Equity Association a non-profit trade association that represents the US healthcare private equity industry Taylor holds an MBA from the Darden Graduate School of Business Administration and a BA from the University of Virginia Taylor previously served on the Board of Directors of the following Charterhouse portfolio companies: The Camelot Schools Cross Country Healthcare and Chamberlin Edmonds Jay Gates Strategic Advisor and Chairman of FrontStreet Management Group (212) 584-3223 Jay Gates joined Charterhouse in 1994 and served as a Managing Director until 2012 when he became a Strategic Advisor to Charterhouse He continues to serve as the Chairman of FrontStreet Management Group a current Charterhouse portfolio company Jay was responsible for sourcing evaluating and executing new platform and add-on investments along with monitoring portfolio company activities within the Business Services sector Jay holds an MBA from New York University Leonard H Stern School of Business and a BA from the State University of New York at Binghamton Jay previously served on the Board of Directors of the following Charterhouse portfolio companies: MP TotalCare Inc LogistiCare Oakleaf Waste Management and Harvard Custom Manufacturing The Information on these pages is intended solely for the benefit of persons who might be aware of investment opportunities that would interest Charterhouse Charterhouses services are provided only to a limited number of private investment funds; Charterhouse does not make its services available to the public ?2012 CHARTERHOUSE EQUITY PARTNERS LLC"], "pageurl": ["http://wwwcharterhouseequitycom/OurTeamhtml"], "siteurl": ["charterhouseequitycom"]}
